   Saatchi Wins Holly Farms
                                                                                                       

   Tyson Foods pulled its $15 million Holly Farms chicken
account from Long, Haymes &amp; Carr, Winston-Salem, N.C., and
awarded it to Saatchi &amp; Saatchi Advertising, New York.
   Tyson acquired Holly Farms last year following a long
takeover fight. Saatchi, a unit of Saatchi &amp; Saatchi Co.,
creates ads for Tyson's other fresh and processed chicken
lines, an account that also bills about $15 million. The
agency created Tyson's "Feeding You Like Family" campaign.
   Jack Dunn, vice president of retail marketing at Tyson,
said the company moved the business to consolidate its
chicken advertising at one agency.
   "Basically, it boils down to getting as few cooks in the
kitchen as we possibly can," Mr. Dunn said. "Saatchi had the
inside track and was doing good work for us." He said the
account was moved without a review.
