   Ad Notes. . . .
                                                                                                       

   GRIFFIN BACAL: Ralston Purina, St. Louis, named Griffin
Bacal, New York, to handle future ad assignments for new
children's food products. It also awarded the shop
agency-of-record status for those products, which may include
breakfast cereals and snacks. Billings haven't been
determined. Griffin Bacal currently handles some ad
assignments for Continental Baking, a Ralston unit.
                                                                                                       

   WHO'S NEWS: At Lintas:USA, four senior vice presidents
were promoted to executive vice president in the shop's media
department. Marc Goldstein was elected executive vice
president, director of national broadcast media and
programming; Carolyn Libby was named executive vice
president, executive media director of Lintas:New York; and
Paul Hunt and Bob Gervason will assume similar positions at
Lintas:Campbell-Ewald in Detroit.
                                                                                                       

   HIP ACCOUNT: Health Insurance Plan (HIP) of Greater New
York, a large East Coast health maintenance organization,
awarded its ad account to TBWA Advertising, New York.
Billings weren't disclosed.
